&lt;p&gt;Emergency Department, Urgent Care Eastbourne District General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister/Charge Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very busy Emergency Department, treating on average 50,000 patients a year. We are looking for a Band 6 Sister / Charge Nurse to join our pro-active and dynamic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly skilled and accomplished Nurse, who is well motivated and committed to high standards of patient care and personal professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a supportive atmosphere, mentorship and clinical supervision within the Clinical Unit and are committed to the professional development of all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team working and Nursing leadership are an integral part of the Unit, and all staff enabled and empowered to make a real difference for their patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates at Band 6 will be able to demonstrate that they can manage a dedicated team to deliver Nursing care of the highest standards to our patients, while working under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimum of 18 months post-qualification experience in an urgent care setting is desirable, as is evidence of Post Registration education such as an Emergency Nursing Module. Potential candidates should also have undertaken their Mentorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion, please contact Any Collis Head of Nursing on 01323 417400 requesting switchboard connect you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
